Breakfast with Curtis
6.9
AdvertisementBy NICOLAS RAPOLDDesultory, dauntingly DIY but secretly efficient, Curtis helps Syd, a mail-order bookseller (played by Theo Green, The acting is as casual as the casting might suggest, at times bewilderingly so, but Ms. Colella appealingly underplays certain moments, as if taking a cue from her characters’ let-it-ride attitude. Curtis gradually blends in and takes things in stride, and that seems a lesson in itself. It’s a film whose seminal event occurred five years earlier, when Syd said an unkind word to Curtis regarding a cat, because, well, that’s how it goes sometimes.




